  "texts": [
    "Research Question 1: Does this strategy generalize to datasets of multiple domains?Table 4 documents the performance of the TXtreme framework which generalizes effectively across multiple domains, achieving superior or highly competitive performance in diverse datasets including solar energy, traffic, electricity and web traffic.",
    "TXtreme achieves the lowest RMSE and MAE, outperforming advanced models DeepAR, N-BEATS, FFNN, and WaveNet.",
    "In particular, it excels in Solar, Traffic, Electricity, and Web Traffic datasets.",
    "The underperformance of models like FFNN, DeepAR, N-BEATS, and WaveNet is due to their focus on general accuracy, which results in a smoothing effect that overlooks extreme values in time series data.",
    "For instance, in datasets with volatile or sporadic spikes, like Web Traffic Weekly, these models may fail to capture the full extent of extreme values, resulting in higher error values compared to the TXtreme."
